</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="16F00DFCFFDD3344FF6AFB167608FA17" pageId="5" pageNumber="200" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5E555E77FFDD3344FF6AFB167608FA17" blockId="5.[174,1233,1236,1519]" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">
D i a g n o s i s. This species can be easily recognized among other 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFDD3344FC39FB1676A7FB77" box="[944,1172,1236,1263]" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFDD3344FC39FB167672FB76" box="[944,1089,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">Campylocera</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
from the 4–5 pairs of very long and strong setae on prementum (
