<paragraph id="5E555E77FFDD3344FF6AFA567079FA77" blockId="5.[174,1233,1236,1519]" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">
R e m a r k s. The abdomen of the only extant 
<typeStatus id="8151E0D5FFDD3344FC98FA56715FFA37" box="[785,876,1428,1455]" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFDD3344FC10FA567680FA36" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1843" box="[921,1203,1428,1454]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFDD3344FC10FA567680FA36" box="[921,1203,1428,1454]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">Campylocera ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is missing (
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFDD3344FE93FA767345FA56" box="[282,374,1460,1487]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,680,702]" captionTargetBox="[280,1119,174,659]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[272,1122,174,674]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Campylocera ferruginea, holotype (MHNP): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — head, left (arrow indicates enlarged setae); 4 — head, anterior view; 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453688/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">
fig. 1, 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFDD3344FEE1FA767345FA56" box="[360,374,1460,1486]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
), but as the extremely long premental setae are known in the only one African species, its identity is clear.
</paragraph>
